body:
#### Issue details

The window isn't restored on the correct monitor if going from fullscreen to windowed.
#### Reproduction steps/code

Execute, immediately drag the window to any non-primary monitor.

``` java
import com.badlogic.gdx.*;
import com.badlogic.gdx.backends.lwjgl.LwjglApplication;
import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.*;
import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.g2d.SpriteBatch;

public class BarebonesBatch extends ApplicationAdapter {
    SpriteBatch batch;
    Texture texture;

    public void create () {
        batch = new SpriteBatch();
        texture = new Texture(Gdx.files.internal("data/badlogic.jpg"));

    }

    int i = 0;

    public void render () {
        i++;
        if (i == 100000) {
            Gdx.graphics.setFullscreenMode(Gdx.graphics.getDisplayMode());
        } else if (i == 200000) {
            Gdx.graphics.setWindowedMode(400,400);
        }
        Gdx.gl.glClear(GL20.GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT);
        batch.begin();
        batch.draw(texture, 100, 100);
        batch.end();
    }

    public static void main (String[] args) throws Exception {
        new LwjglApplication(new BarebonesBatch());
    }
}
```
#### Version of LibGDX and/or relevant dependencies

1.9.4
